    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-mushroom-shawarma-with-garlic-mayo-and-chips/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>sliced red onion</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>sugar </strong>and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled red onion</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-mushroom-shawarma-with-garlic-mayo-and-chips/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>Fable pulled mushrooms </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for an initial 5-6 min or until browned</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-mushroom-shawarma-with-garlic-mayo-and-chips/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel lengths off your <strong>cucumber</strong> until you end up with a pile of cucumber ribbons</p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-mushroom-shawarma-with-garlic-mayo-and-chips/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>grated garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) with your <strong>mayo</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> in a bowl and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic mayo</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-mushroom-shawarma-with-garlic-mayo-and-chips/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms have browned, add your <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground smoked paprika </strong>and <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of oil if the pan is looking a little dry</p><p>Add your <strong>wholemeal pittas</strong> to a <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-mushroom-shawarma-with-garlic-mayo-and-chips/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, transfer the mushrooms to a clean board and shred apart using two forks - this technique is known as 'pulling' \u2013 these are your <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>pulled mushrooms</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pulled-mushroom-shawarma-with-garlic-mayo-and-chips/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To assemble, load the <strong>toasted pittas</strong> with the <strong>spiced pulled mushrooms</strong>, <strong>quick-pickled red onion</strong> and <strong>cucumber ribbons </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>pulled mushroom shawarmas</strong></p><p>Top the <strong>pulled mushroom shawarmas </strong>with a dollop of<strong> garlic mayo</strong> and serve with the <strong>chips </strong>and<strong> salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
